reviews.review_text:
Thank you... ...Matthew Vernon, Charlie Miller and whoever else uploaded this show! This and 9/12/88 are my two favorite under the radar shows, at least according to DeadBase, neither one registering at least two votes to garner a mention on what was voted favorite of '88.

Pretty amazing I say as this show, the 3rd of nine that year at MSG, was pretty much hands down my favorite of them all and I attended all of them. It felt like the energy was ready to be taken to another level after the 1st two nights and imho this most excellent recording proves me out. The hitting the restart button with the 1/2 Step following the initial Hey Pocky Way>Minglewood opener. For someone that was not particularly interested in Bobby's cowboy songs at the time, this Uncle>Mexicali was particularly snazzy. To Lay Me Down was its usual beautiful self and Masterpiece was a popping version. Bird Song was really, really good.

China/Rider simply galloped by its end, the drummers made this one extra special. The Ship Of Fools was one of the two best I feel I've been in the building for (the other being 9/19/90) and felt that the set lost zero momentum with its placement as it could have.

Estimated>Terrapin is my favorite pairing of the two songs and felt the execution of both songs were full and on point leading to a very engaging Drums/Space then it was pretty much the Bobby and Brent show starting with Miracle>Fantasy/Jude and one of my favorite if not my all time favorite Sugar Mags, Bobby was in full rock star mode and I clearly remember him working the audience into a frenzy with a wicked grin on his face during the SSDD part and Jerry acting as the straight man on the side, simply laying down his best rock and roll licks for it. A beautifully rendered Baby Blue sent the packed house out happily into a beautiful late Summer night. I was so happily tripped out that night that I walked home, across the 59th Street Bridge to my apartment in Queens a couple of miles inland.

I believe that this show is definitely worth your time and attention. Peace out!
